<li>My heart aches for you.  Let me know if there is anything at all I can do.</li>
<li>Sending you strength and comfort during this difficult time.</li>
<li>I can't imagine what you're going through, but I'm here for you.</li>
<li>Thinking of you and sending all my love.</li>
<li>Please know that I am here for you, always.</li>
<li>So sorry to hear about [deceased's name]. They will be missed.</li>
<li>I'll always remember [deceased's name]'s [positive memory].</li>
<li>Sending you lots of love and support.</li>
<li>I'm here if you need someone to talk to, cry with, or just sit in silence with.</li>
<li>Your friendship means so much to me, and I'm here for you.</li>
<li>May beautiful memories of [deceased's name] bring you comfort.</li>
<li>Please accept my deepest condolences.</li>
<li>I'm so incredibly sorry for your loss.</li>
    

      <h2 id="expressions-of-support-during-loss">Expressions of Support During Loss</h2>
      <p></p>
<p>Offering practical support can be as meaningful as words of comfort.  Let the bereaved know you're willing to assist with tasks, errands, or emotional support.  Keep your offer open-ended and avoid being intrusive.</p>
<li>I’m thinking of you and offering any support I can during this time.</li>
<li>Please let me know if you need help with anything – errands, meals, etc.</li>
<li>I'm happy to help in any way I can.  Don't hesitate to reach out.</li>
<li>Sending you love and support. Please don't hesitate to ask for anything.</li>
<li>I'm here for you, whether you need someone to talk to or help with practical things.</li>
<li>Let me know if there's anything I can do to make things easier.</li>
<li>I'm happy to run errands, bring over meals, or simply keep you company.</li>
<li> I’m here to listen, offer help, or just be present.</li>
<li> Thinking of you. Please accept my heartfelt condolences and know I am here for you.</li>
<li> Please don't hesitate to call if you need anything at all.</li>
<li>My deepest sympathy.  Let me know if I can assist in any way, big or small.</li>
<li> Please reach out if there's anything I can help with.</li>
<li>Sending you strength and support.</li>
<li> I'm available if you need a shoulder to cry on or an ear to listen.</li>
<li> I'm here to support you in any way possible.</li>
    
    
    
